{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "With sufficient evaluation and validation, these tools could be standardized and are scalable.",
    "Speech recognition models (Radford et al., 2022), speech transcription (OpenAI, 2022), and multilingual translation (Google, 2025) tools pave the way for Application Programming Interfaces (APIs) that can transcribe speech using the International Phonetic Alphabet and conduct preliminary screenings for articulation, language, voice and fluency disorders.",
    "An SLP may not need multiple, single purpose software.",
    "These tools may be deployed in schools and pediatric clinics to not only help identify children with some speech and language issue but also to identify children with multilingual background who may need further evaluation.",
    "In early childhood settings, pre-kindergarten play sessions may be audio-and video-recorded (with appropriate permissions), to recognize, transcribe, and analyze speech and language using pre-trained NLP, SLM agents."
  ],
